The paper deals with matching problems in bipartite graphs with preference lists, which is a classic topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of popular matchings is also relevant to social choice theory (cs.DM). The paper proposes a new subclass of popular matchings called dominant matchings, which is a novel contribution to the field and may be of interest to researchers in data structures (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.SI).
